ate Students will be offered entirely online during Summer Session II (8-week session, June 15 – August 7, 2020).  Registration for GC 509 is available now in UIC’s course registration system.  For the latest campus updates on the coronavirus situation and the Graduate College’s list of COVID-19 policies and graduate student resources, please visit the links below.           UIC COVID-19 Website         Graduate College COVID-19 Updates and Resources         Welcome to the International Teaching Assistant Program website!      As a part of UIC’s Graduate College, the International Teaching Assistant Program provides three main services for international teaching assistants (ITAs) and the academic departments that employ them:   conducting oral English proficiency testing for all non-native English-speaking TAs in compliance with Illinois state law  providing courses to help ITAs improve their English language, communication, and teaching skills  offering drop-in workshops and casual social events to give ITAs more opportunities to use their English outside of the classroom   We also organize and run the annual Campus-Wide New TA Orientation .  Note:  The ITA Program does not currently have any available TA positions and does not assist graduate students in finding TA positions.    Oral English Proficiency Testing    ITA English Support Courses    ITA Events           Information on the Campus-Wide New TA Orientation                     UIC Logo         Graduate  College           ITAP Resources    Oral English Proficiency Testing    ITA Courses    ITA Workshops and Events    Useful Information for New ITAs      UIC Resources    Academic Calendar    ACCC    Graduate College    UIC Pop-Up Food Pantry    Wellness Center    Writing Center         Contact   International Teaching Assistant Program  1200 W. Harrison St., 1190 SSB, Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 413-2235  itap@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Ath